---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Stackin Paper | ML Research Portfolio">
  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 font-sans text-slate-900">
    <header class="mb-8">
		<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-serif italic tracking-tight text-[#bdaa8b]">
			Stackin Paper: Building on ML Research
		</h1>
	</header>
		
	<p class="text-xl leading-relaxed text-slate-700 mb-8">
		Welcome to <strong>Stackin Paper(s)</strong>! This is my personal playground for breaking down the latest machine learning research papers, implementing them from scratch, and bridging the gap between intertwined topics; all while documenting my findings along the way.
	</p>


	<h3 class="text-xl md:text-3xl text-[#bdaa8b] tracking-tight mt-12 mb-2 font-serif underline">
		Objectives
	</h3>
	
	<p class="text-xl leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
		When tasked with explaining my objectives for this endeavor, I fall back to a quote from one of my favorite shows, Bleach, to offer some insight:
	</p>

	<section class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-6 my-3 italic text-slate-700">
		"I dislike perfection. If something is perfect, there is nothing above it. There is no room for imagination. No space for intelligence or ability. [...] Be more wonderful than anything that existed before you, but never perfect."
	</section>

	<p class="text-xl leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
		I have squandered much of my time in the pursuit of perfection; always planning, rarely executing. My hope with this venture is to change that. To embrace imperfection, and the rich trove of experiences that resides within the pitfalls of mistakes. 
	</p>

  <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed text-slate-700 mt-4">
		Over the course of this next chapter, I hope to make many, <i>many</i>, <b>many</b> mistakes. More importantly, I hope to use these mistakes as fuel to light the path for my future explorations !
	</p>

  <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed text-slate-700 mt-4">
    Consequently, through these future explorations, I aim to build a solid foundation for algorithmic and practical rigor; and gain insight on research taste. I have many opinions on what this topic of 'taste' truly entails, but I will leave that perhaps for a future article :)
  </p>

    <section class="mt-12 mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-3xl text-[#bdaa8b] tracking-tight mt-12 mb-2 font-serif underline">🗂️ Research Logs</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-slate-100">
              <th class="p-3 border">Date</th>
              <th class="p-3 border">Paper / Topic</th>
              <th class="p-3 border">Key Concepts</th>
              <th class="p-3 border">Action</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-3 border font-bold">Feb 2026</td>
              <td class="p-3 border italic">Gradient Regularization w/ DR.GRPO</td>
              <td class="p-3 border text-sm text-slate-600">GRPO, Optimization</td>
              <td class="p-3 border text-blue-600 font-semibold"><a href="/projects">View Project</a></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="text-slate-400">
              <td class="p-3 border italic">Upcoming</td>
              <td class="p-3 border">Experiential RL</td>
              <td class="p-3 border text-sm">RL</td>
              <td class="p-3 border italic">WIP</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-3xl text-[#bdaa8b] tracking-tight mt-6 mb-2 font-serif underline">🏗️ Repository Structure</h2>
      <pre class="bg-slate-900 text-slate-100 p-6 rounded-lg font-mono text-sm overflow-x-auto">
stackin-paper/
├── shared_utils/         &lt;- Custom loaders &amp; metrics
├── Gradient-Reg/    	  &lt;- Project Folder
│   ├── README.md         &lt;- The article/notes
│   ├── requirements.txt  &lt;- Isolated deps
│   └── src/              &lt;- Implementation code
└── ...</pre>
    </section>

	<section>
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-3xl text-[#bdaa8b] tracking-tight mt-14 mb-2 font-serif underline">🤖 AI Disclosure</h2>
      <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed text-slate-700 mb-4">
		I will try to be as transparent as possible regarding my usage of AI where relevant. While it can certainly be tempting to speed up progress and rely entirely on AI to implement these papers, my pursuit of imperfection leaves me seemingly orthogonal to this predisposition.
	  </p>
	  <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed text-slate-700 mb-4">
	  	How can I learn, make mistakes, and be perfectly imperfect without touching upon the work myself ? The extent of my AI usage (unless specified otherwise, which I will explicitly do so where necessary) is to review & refine my conceptual understanding at the start of the project, and verify key implementation details at the end.
	  </p>
	  <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
		Well, that and also this entire website was coded using AI. I am not a frontend developer :)
	  </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>